## 1. Dataset

The audio-feature CSV `TruerChordAnalysis3justzuto.csv` contains
**`r nrow(raw)`** tracks across three artists, after dropping
malformed rows. Track counts:

```{r}
artist_counts(raw) |> kable()
```

## 2. Variable consolidation

The raw file ships **101** columns. Many are redundant, sparse, or
collinear with each other. The decisions made (in
`R/02_consolidate.R`) were:

| Group | Action | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| `artist`, `Zuttomayo`, `artist_yorushika` | dropped | redundant with `artist_canonical` |
| `scale` | dropped | already encoded by `scale_root` + `scale_mode` |
| `mode_*_match` (×13) | dropped | highly collinear; the dominant mode is in `scale_mode` |
| `primary_function_ratio` | dropped | exactly = `tonic + dominant + subdominant` ratios |
| `chord_diversity` | dropped | collinear with integer `unique_chords` |
| `band_brilliance_ratio` | dropped | the seven band ratios sum to 1 — drop one to break collinearity |
| `energy_start`, `energy_end` | dropped | re-encoded by `energy_buildup`; `energy_mid` retained |
| `mfcc_*_std` | dropped | means kept; std mostly redundant for genre-scale separation |
| `inst_music` | dropped | near-constant (≈1 for every track) |
| 30 individual `inst_*` probabilities | **rolled up** | summed into 7 instrument families: guitars, bass, bowed strings, keys, drums, winds/brass, vocals |

The final feature matrix has **`r length(consol$numeric_cols)`**
numeric variables × **`r nrow(consol$data)`** tracks.

## 3. PCA

```{r}
pca_res$var_exp |>
  head(8) |>
  mutate(variance_explained = scales::percent(variance_explained, 0.1),
         cumulative         = scales::percent(cumulative, 0.1)) |>
  kable(caption = "Variance explained by the first 8 components")
```

PC1 alone captures
**`r scales::percent(pca_res$var_exp$variance_explained[1], 0.1)`** of
the total variance; PC1+PC2 together capture
**`r scales::percent(sum(pca_res$var_exp$variance_explained[1:2]), 0.1)`**.

